Day 1
From each plates containing your mutants, pick 3 individual colonies and inoculate it into a 15mL falcon tube containing 2mL of TB broth with 2uL of kanamycin. ***This steps require sterile technique
Incubate at 37*C for overnight. 

Day 2
If you are not ready to perform the mini-prep step, spin down your cells (dispose of the supernatant) and store it in -20*C.
Otherwise, review and follow the miniprep procedures to extract your DNA. 
Once you have miniprep all your samples, send the products for sequence verifications. 
